-- SEC to hold news conference on regulation merger
-- 
-- Tue Nov 28, 2006 9:56am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2006/11/28/us-financial-nyse-sec-idUSN2822656620061128

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - The U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission said on Tuesday it will hold a news conference at 10:30 a.m. EST (1530 GMT) on the plan by the NASD and NYSE Group Inc. NYX.N to merge self-regulation units. 

 The merger will create a single organization to oversee all securities firms doing business with the public in the United States. Appearing at the news conference will be NASD Chairman Mary Schapiro, NYSE Regulation Inc. Chief Executive Richard Ketchum, and SEC Chairman Christopher Cox, among others, the SEC said.